(1, 'Active', '2014-07-14 14:39:00', 'YES', '2014-01-09 15:00:00', 'Active', 'a6654fca9438810e8d4ffce3ff3c05b7.png', 'knewdog.com Blog: How to reduce noise?', 'reduce noise', 'Do you suffer from stress due to too much information? I show you a solution concerning email handling that you might want to apply to reduce noise, get more done and be more relaxed.', 'How to reduce noise?', '<h2>Do you suffer from stress due to too much information?</h2>\n\n<p><strong>Feeling overwhelmed due to the informational noise around you? First be assured, this is normal. Most of us would have this problem when being in your situation. Humans are only made for a certain number of transactions per hour and we have not been built as information consumers, but as hunters and gatherers. So the problem is not you, but strategies and tactics you apply concerning the treatment of information. And that can easily be learned.</strong></p>\n\n<p>Today I would like to show you a solution concerning email handling that you might want to apply to reduce noise, get more done and be more relaxed.</p>\n\n<p>One major lever if you want to become really more productive lies in noise reduction. In order to reduce the noise from your in-box it is important that</p>\n\n<ol style="margin-left:30px">\n	<li>You switch off the email reminder and check you in-box all 2 hours or so, but not more often.</li>\n	<li>You use filters, so that only things pop up in your in-box which are really important and actionable. For example you could filter every newsletter, so that they go directly into your &ldquo;to read&rdquo; folder.</li>\n	<li>You practice the in-box zero principle. After reading a mail you either delete it or put it into a folder for further reference, take action immediately or setup a task from it in order to do it later and then store it with the task.</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>You still believe that all your mails are time-sensitive and require immediate action? Here is my suggestion to cure you from this often false believe. Check email urgency yourself one day and make a list. On the left side, you check, when you read a mail, but do nothing with it. On the right side you check when you take action immediately and 2 hours later would have been too late. I bet that for 95% of all people the right side stays empty.</p>\n\n<p>You have a job (flight controller, security agent, police officer,...) where you need to react to some of the emails immediately. Then there are 2 solutions. Either set an email filter that make ring an alarm if one of these emails arrives. The other solution is to ask a colleague to keep an eye on your in-box for 2 hours, so you can work on the important things and vice versa.</p>\n\n<p>This tipp was based on a great <strong><a href="http://www.preneurmedia.tv/preneurcast/preneurcast003-information-overload-email-a-go-go/" style="color: gray;" target="_blank">podcast from Pete Williams of Preneurmedia</a></strong>. By the way, you can find <strong><a href="https://www.knewdog.com/preneur-marketing/" style="color: gray;" target="_blank">Pete&rsquo;s newsletter</a></strong> in our online newsletter library too.</p>\n\n<p>And don&rsquo;t forget that using knewdog would help you filter and manage your newsletters in a quick and easy way. <strong><a href="https://www.knewdog.com/home/about/" style="color: gray;" title="What for?">Click here to learn how it works!</a></strong></p>\n\n<p>I would be happy to read your comments.</p>\n\n<p>Enjoy your day!<br />\nYour knewdog! Team</p>\n', 'Wie kann ich den Informationsl√§rm reduzieren?', '<h2>Du kriegst nichts mehr &bdquo;gebacken&ldquo;? Wirst von den Unmengen an Mails f&ouml;rmlich erschlagen?</h2>\n\n<p><span style="font-family:arial"><strong>Du f&uuml;hlst dich &uuml;berfordert von den vielen E-Mails die du jeden Tag bekommst? Dein E-Mail Postfach gleicht mehr einem Bermuda-Dreieck, als einem Arbeitsmittel. Das nennt man Informationsl&auml;rm. Die meisten von uns haben dieses Problem. Menschen sind einfach nur f&uuml;r eine gewisse Anzahl an Transaktionen pro Stunde gebaut und auch nicht als Informationsverarbeiter, sondern als J&auml;ger und Sammler. Das Problem bist also nicht du, sondern Deine Strategien und Taktiken, die du bei der Informationsverarbeitung anwendest. Diese Strategien und Taktiken kann man leicht erlernen.</strong></span></p>\n\n<p>Heute m&ouml;chte ich dir eine L&ouml;sung zum Thema E-Mail zeigen die Du vielleicht anwenden m&ouml;chtest, um den L&auml;rm effizient zu verringern, mehr zu schaffen und entspannter durch den Tag zu kommen.</p>\n\n<p>Der gr&ouml;&szlig;te Hebel, um den Informationsl&auml;rm in den Griff zu bekommen und wirklich mehr zu schaffen, liegt in der Reduzierung dieser Ger&auml;uschkulisse. Um dieses Problem in den Griff zu bekommen, solltest du folgende 3 Aktionen umsetzen:</p>\n\n<ol style="margin-left:30px">\n	<li>Schalte die E-Mail Benachrichtigung ab und kontrolliere dein Postfach alle 2 Stunden aber nicht &ouml;fter.</li>\n	<li>Verwende Filter, damit nur noch die Dinge in deinem Posteingang landen, die aktionsbezogen und wichtig sind. Newsletter kannst du zum Beispiel automatisch in einen &ldquo;Lesen&rdquo; Ordner verschieben.</li>\n	<li>Verwende das Prinzip des leeren Postfachs. Wenn du eine Mail gelesen hast, l&ouml;sche sie, verschiebe sie in ein Verzeichnis, falls du sie sp&auml;ter als Referenz brauchst, erledige die Aufgabe sofort oder lege eine Aufgabe in deiner Aufgabenplanung an und speichere die Mail mit der Aufgabe.</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>Du glaubst, du musst alle Mails sofort lesen, weil sie wichtig und zeitkritisch sind? Dann beobachte dich einmal einen Tag und mache eine Strichliste. Links ein Strich, wenn du eine Mail zwar gelesen, aber nicht unmittelbar reagiert hast. Rechts ein Strich, wenn du sofort eine Aktion gestartet hast und es 2 Stunden sp&auml;ter bereits zu sp&auml;t gewesen w&auml;re. Bei 95% aller Menschen bleibt die rechte Seite leer.</p>\n\n<p>Deine rechte Seite ist nicht leer, weil es ein paar E-Mails pro Tag gibt, auf die du auf jeden Fall und sofort reagieren musst? Dann gibt es 2 M&ouml;glichkeiten, damit du dennoch effizient arbeiten kannst. Erstens k&ouml;nntest du einen Filter erstellen, der die wirklich eiligen Mails herausfiltert und daf&uuml;r sorgt, dass dann ein Alarm angeht. Die andere L&ouml;sung ist, einen Kollegen zu bitten, deine Mails f&uuml;r 2 Stunden zu checken. In dieser Zeit kannst du effizient arbeiten und am n&auml;chsten Tag macht ihr es umgekehrt.</p>\n\n<p>Dieser Tipp basiert auf einem gro&szlig;artigen englischsprachigen&nbsp;<strong><a href="http://www.preneurmedia.tv/preneurcast/preneurcast003-information-overload-email-a-go-go/" style="color: gray;" target="_blank">Podcast von Pete Williams von Preneurmedia</a></strong>. &Uuml;brigens, den&nbsp;<strong><a href="https://www.knewdog.com/preneur-marketing/" style="color: gray;">Newsletter von Pete Williams</a></strong>&nbsp;findest du auch in unserer Newsletter-Bibliothek.</p>\n\n<p>Und vergiss nicht, dass knewdog dir helfen kann, deine Newsletter auf einfache und schnelle Art zu filtern und zu managen.&nbsp;<strong><a href="https://www.knewdog.com/home/about/?lang=de" style="color: gray;" title="What for?">Klicke hier um zu erfahren, wie es funktioniert!</a></strong></p>\n\n<p>Ich freue mich auf eure Kommentare.</p>\n\n<p>Genie&szlig;t den Tag.<br />\nEuer knewdog! Team</p>\n', '', '', '', ''),
(3, 'Active', '2014-07-14 14:33:00', 'YES', '2013-05-28 16:00:00', 'Active', '', 'knewdog.com Blog: We launched knewdog to prevent you from spam', 'spam', 'knewdog! is a platform which protects the users, keeps your email address private and never ever allow any spam to be sent to you.', 'Why did we launch knewdog?', '<div class="entry-content cf">\n<p><span style="font-family:arial"><strong>Did you ever order a newsetter?</strong> Well I did. It was a newsletter about hotels in France. Why? I wanted to travel to France and looked for good deals. After coming back home I tried to cancel the newsletter. Yes, it had an unsubscribe link, <small><small><small><small><small>a very small one</small></small></small></small></small>, but it had one. The link led to a &ldquo;page not found&rdquo; page. So I put it in my blacklist. Some weeks later, I got aware that I received hotel information from London. London?! I had no intention to go there. And it went on and on. Like a never ending nightmare. </span></p>\n\n<p>As this happened not only once, but several times, I started to think about a solution. And did quite some research on the Web. I didn&rsquo;t find anything, apart hundreds of sites who promoted how easy it would be to get your newsletter out to thousands of people. That was not really the answer I was looking for.<br />\n<strong>What about my right to just receive the information I want and nothing more? And the right to get rid of any newsletter at any time? What about my right to use my time as I want to? Cleaning up my inbox is clearly nothing I would like to spend time on.</strong></p>\n\n<p>That was when I decided to launch<strong> knewdog!, a platform which would protect the users.</strong> Where you can just read the newsletter you want to read and when you want to read them. That would keep your email address private, never ever allow any spam to be sent to you. That would allow you to read whatever you want without someone spying you. A platform which will allow you to gain back your informational sovereignty.<br />\nAnd that&rsquo;s what knewdog! is all about. <strong>The first newsletter platform designed for newsletter readers and not for senders.</strong></p>\n\n<p>Take pleasure reading!</p>\n\n<p>Your knewdog! Team</p>\n</div>\n', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(4, 'Active', '2014-07-07 13:02:00', 'YES', '2014-07-07 14:00:00', 'Active', 'c3b7982dc2f6356b3832db88779d8ae4.png', 'knewdog.com Blog: Some words about our newsletter library', 'newsletter library', 'Be a part of the knewdog community from the very beginning and sign up today! We only can fight spam successfully together with you. Let''s do it!', 'Some words about our newsletter library', '<div class="entry-content cf">\n<p><span style="font-family:arial"><strong>If you check out our newsletter library you might say &ldquo;Hey, these are big words, but there are only a few newsletters in your database. This is not enough!&rdquo; And you are right.</strong></span></p>\n\n<p>Our answer is twofold.</p>\n\n<p><span style="font-family:arial">First, <strong>i</strong></span><span style="font-family:arial"><span style="font-family:arial"><strong>f you are missing a newsletter</strong> on our platform, just send us an email and we <strong>will order it for you</strong>, so you can read it online or even download it. So if you stumble upon a website with an interesting newsletter, just contact us and put the URL of the page in the content of your email to us. As soon as we have ordered it and received the first version we will inform you that the newsletter is available for you. As there are virtually hundreds of thousands of newsletters out there waiting to be read, <strong>we need your help</strong>, as it would be a mission impossible to find the most interesting ones for you.</span></span></p>\n\n<p>Second, knewdog is still a newborn baby and <strong>we just started this website</strong>. This is not an excuse, this is a fact. We are well aware, that some people might be disappointed. The problem is, we had to start at zero and to develop the platform which takes time and money.</p>\n\n<h3>The prelaunch version</h3>\n\n<p>In a first step, we only had kind of prelaunch version online to test the market and to find out, if there is enough interest out there to justify the spending of many thousands of Dollars or Euros to program a website that will do all the nice things that we want to do. If there were just some people we still would continue to maintain the website and develop it, but it would never get all the functions that would make it a real working tool. It was not an easy decision between just programming a subscription side with nothing else behind or setting up a website which would at least provide some basic functionalities. We chose the second way. For us it seemed to be the more serious way to <strong>show our commitment</strong>. The objective was to get to know if there are people out there having the same problem like we did and not finding a solution. We fixed our target to 100 subscribers. Only people we do not know counted.<strong> It only took some days to prove that there is interest and we decided to launch the programming</strong>.</p>\n\n<h3>Ready to rumble</h3>\n\n<p>Now we have finished the programming of the first real working version of knewdog and you have all the features you need and even more. And the good thing is, that every subscriber who supported us in this prelaunch phase gets a one year pro account subscription for free. Just to thank you for your support. For all new users, subscription is still free.</p>\n\n<h3>We still need your support!</h3>\n\n<p>But we still need your help to make this project a success. Let us know which newsletters you want us to integrate in our library. Send us your feedback. <strong>Be a part of the knewdog community from the very beginning and sign up today!</strong> We only can fight spam successfully together with you. Let&#39;s do it!</p>\n\n<p>And don&#39;t forget to tell your friends about ist!</p>\n\n<p>Your knewdog! Team</p>\n</div>\n', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(7, 'Active', '2014-07-14 14:41:00', 'YES', '2013-09-25 15:00:00', 'Active', '', 'Press release 2013-09: knewdog reaches its first 100 subscribers', 'press release', 'Press release 2013-09: knewdog reaches its first milestone of 100 registered users and starts further development. For the development of its final version knewdog invites professional freelancers and students to join the development team.', 'knewdog reaches its first milestone of 100 registered users and starts further development', '<h2><span style="font-family:arial"><strong>Press release 2013-09</strong></span></h2>\n\n<p><strong>knewdog, the independent newsletter platform, up to now only available as Prelaunch Version with limited functionalities, celebrates its first 100 subscribers. The current website aimed to find out, if there was enough interest in the market to justify the spending of many thousands of Dollars or Euros to program the final website. The first milestone for this market test was to reach 100 subscribers to prove the interest in this service.</strong></p>\n\n<p><span style="font-family:arial"><span style="font-family:arial">Ines Sachs, director of knewdog, says: &ldquo;The first step is done; we now know that there is interest in the market. This conclusion was absolutely vital for us to convince ourselves and to cement our commitment for this project. We are very excited to see that out there there are people asking for a solution for the problem of newsletter management. We will now launch the programming. The Prelaunch Version will remain online in-between so that visitors can sign up free and benefit from our special offer to get a one year free Premium account as soon as the final version will be available.&rdquo;</span></span></p>\n\n<p>For the development of its final version knewdog invites professional freelancers and students to join the development team. The following expertise is requested:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>WordPress is and should remain the basis of the website, so expert knowledge of the WordPress Database System is essential</li>\n	<li>Pre-existing and ready programmed plugins have to be used and refined to economize time and money</li>\n	<li>SEO knowledge is required; the website must respect the newest search engine exigencies</li>\n	<li>The communication of the team will be made in English, so fluent English is vital</li>\n	<li>A proof of the expertise of the candidate is requested in terms of verifiable references and links</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><span style="font-family:arial">Ines: &ldquo;To make it clear from the beginning: We won&rsquo;t spend money for highly sophisticated flashy useless features. The first objective is to get started quickly and to provide users with the basic functionalities. If you want to join the team, we&rsquo;ll double your hourly rate if you&rsquo;re ready to accept payment on success. This project could be very interesting for a student&rsquo;s internship as well and we promise a certificate and a positive reference.&rdquo;</span></p>\n\n<p>Quotation procedure starts now. Everyone interested in making an offer is invited to contact knewdog and request the specification sheet: <a href="https://www.knewdog.com/contact/" title="CONTACT">CONTACT</a></p>\n\n<p>...................................................</p>\n\n<p>This press release has been published on <a href="http://www.prlog.org/12215369-knewdog-reaches-its-first-milestone-of-100-registered-users-and-starts-further-development.html" target="_blank" title="Press release on PRLog">PRLog, Sep. 24, 2013</a>.</p>\n', 'knewdog erreicht den ersten Meilenstein von 100 Registrierungen und startet die Weiterentwicklung', '<h2>Pressemitteilung 09/2013</h2>\n\n<p><span style="font-family:arial"><strong>knewdog, die unabh&auml;ngige Newsletter-Plattform, bisher nur als Prelaunch-Version mit eingeschr&auml;nkter Funktionalit&auml;t verf&uuml;gbar, feiert seine ersten 100 registrierten Nutzer. Die aktuelle Website hatte das Ziel herauszufinden, ob auf dem Markt ein ausreichend gro&szlig;es Interesse, um die Investition von Tausenden von Dollars oder Euros in die Entwicklung der endg&uuml;ltigen Version zu rechtfertigen. Der erste Meilenstein f&uuml;r diesen Markttest bestand darin, mit 100 registrierten Nutzern ein ausreichendes Interesse zu beweisen.</strong></span></p>\n\n<p>Ines Sachs, Direktor von knewdog, sagt: &bdquo;Der erste Schritt ist getan; wir wissen nun, dass Interesse im Markt besteht. Diese Erkenntnis war absolut vital f&uuml;r uns, um uns selbst zu &uuml;berzeugen und unser Commitment f&uuml;r das Projekt zu st&auml;rken. Wir sind begeistert, dass es da drau&szlig;en Leute gibt, die nach einer L&ouml;sung f&uuml;r das Problem des Newsletter-Managements suchen. Wir werden nun mit der Programmierung beginnen. Die Prelaunch-Version wird in der Zwischenzeit online bleiben, so dass Besucher sich kostenlos registrieren und von unserem Sonderangebot profitieren k&ouml;nnen, eine einj&auml;hrige kostenlose Premium-Mitgliedschaft zu erhalten, sobald die endg&uuml;ltige Version unserer Website online ist.&ldquo;</p>\n\n<p><span style="font-family:arial"><span style="font-family:arial">F&uuml;r die Entwicklung seiner endg&uuml;ltigen Version sucht knewdog Unterst&uuml;tzung durch Freelancer und Praktikanten f&uuml;r das Entwicklungsteam. Die folgenden F&auml;higkeiten werden gefordert:</span></span></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>WordPress ist aktuell und in Zukunft die Basis der Website, Expertenwissen des WordPress Datenbank-Systems ist entscheidend</li>\n	<li>Bereits existierende und fertig programmierte Plugins sind zu nutzen und auszubauen, um Zeit und Geld zu sparen</li>\n	<li>SEO-Wissen wird gefordert, die Website muss den neuesten Suchmaschinen-Anforderungen gerecht werden</li>\n	<li>Die Kommunikation im Team wird auf Englisch erfolgen, flie&szlig;ende Englisch-Kenntnisse sind vital</li>\n	<li>Ein Nachweis der Expertise des Kandidaten wird in Form von nachpr&uuml;fbaren Referenzen und Links gefordert</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Ines: &bdquo;Um es von vorne herein klar zu machen: Wir werden kein Geld ausgeben f&uuml;r hochgradig komplexe, bunt blinkende, nutzlose Funktionen. Unser erstes Ziel ist es, schnell zu starten und den Nutzern die Grundfunktionen zu bieten. Wenn Sie Interesse an einer Zusammenarbeit haben, verdoppeln wir Ihren bisherigen Stundensatz, falls Sie bereit sind, eine erfolgsabh&auml;ngige Bezahlung zu akzeptieren. Dieses Projekt k&ouml;nnte auch als Praktikum f&uuml;r Studenten interessant sein. Wir versprechen ein positives Referenzschreiben und eine Praktikumsbest&auml;tigung.&ldquo;</p>\n\n<p>Die Angebotsphase beginnt jetzt. Interessenten werden gebeten, mit knewdog Kontakt aufzunehmen und das Lastenhaft anzufordern: <a href="https://www.knewdog.com/contact/?lang=de" title="KONTAKT">KONTAKT</a></p>\n\n<p>...................................................</p>\n\n<p>Diese Pressemitteilung wurde ver&ouml;ffentlicht auf <a href="http://www.openpr.de/news/751817.html" target="_blank" title="Pressemitteilung auf openPR">openPR, Sep. 24, 2013</a>.</p>\n', '', '', '', '');
