(242, 'AUG1441810N', 'AUG1441810N140815080126', 'parent', 'autonews@crainnewsalerts.com', 0, 'NO', 'Automotive News China', 'Highlights from top manufacturer and supplier news in greater China', 'Yang Jian', '<p><em>Automotive News China</em> is published by the Automotive News Group of Crain Communications Inc. In addition to a full staff of correspondents inside China, it also draws upon the editorial resources of sister publications <em>Automotive News, Automotive News Europe </em>and <em>Automobilwoche</em>. The Automotive News Group has an unrivaled worldwide network of reporters and editors, providing broad coverage for readers.</p>\n', 'http://crainnewsalerts.com/portal/unsubscribeconfirm', 'Open in a web browser', '45', '200233', 'Shanghai', '', 1, '12,17', '20,21,2,23,22', 'Automotive News China', 'NO', '0', 'http://www.autonewschina.com', '', '2b08c9093e8fe35506d266ee9f57a590.jpg', '<p>Commentary by journalist Yang Jian and highlights from top manufacturer and supplier news in greater China. <em>Automotive News China</em> is a free, weekly newsletter delivered via e-mail to more than 20,000 Chinese automotive industry executives and global automotive executives with responsibility for the Chinese market.</p>\n\n<p>It covers domestic Chinese automakers (SAIC, First Automotive Works, Chery, Geely, etc.) who export vehicles worldwide as well as the purchasing operations of global automakers (General Motors, Volkswagen, Toyota, etc.) that do business in China. It also covers global suppliers (Aisin Seiki, Faurecia, Lear, Visteon, etc.) who make auto parts in China for export to North America, Europe and Japan, as well as domestic Chinese suppliers (Wanxiang Group, Chongqing Tsingshan, Tianjin Automotive, Guizhou Honghu, etc.) who sell to automakers in China and worldwide.</p>\n', '', '', '', '', 0, '', '', '', 'several times per week', 0, '2014-08-15 08:01:26', '2014-08-06 07:02:12', 'Active');
